Sentencas: In order to reduce the operating temperature of solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs), a proton conductive oxide deposited on Pd was proposed as an electrolyte.
Titulo: Low Temperature Operation of Solid Oxide Fuel Cells (SOFCs) with Proton Conductive Electrolyte Deposited on Pd Foil Substrates

Sentencas: Two types of (La0.6Sr0.4)(Co0.2Fe0.8)O3-delta (LSCF) were used as cathode and compared to reveal the effect of the cathode texture.
Titulo: Low Temperature Operation of Solid Oxide Fuel Cells (SOFCs) with Proton Conductive Electrolyte Deposited on Pd Foil Substrates

Sentencas: One is the films with dense structure prepared by pulsed laser deposition and the other is films with columnar structure prepared by rf-magnetron sputtering method.
Titulo: Low Temperature Operation of Solid Oxide Fuel Cells (SOFCs) with Proton Conductive Electrolyte Deposited on Pd Foil Substrates

Sentencas: In comparing the power generation properties at 600 and 650 degrees C, the SOFC with sputtered cathode showed higher OCV and power generation than those of the SOFC with the PLD deposited cathode.
Titulo: Low Temperature Operation of Solid Oxide Fuel Cells (SOFCs) with Proton Conductive Electrolyte Deposited on Pd Foil Substrates

Sentencas: This indicates the importance of oxygen supply at the reaction field using cathode with columnar structure.
Titulo: Low Temperature Operation of Solid Oxide Fuel Cells (SOFCs) with Proton Conductive Electrolyte Deposited on Pd Foil Substrates
